com.versant.fund
Interface SessionWithDatabase

All Superinterfaces:
ClassBuilder
All Known Subinterfaces:
Session
public interface SessionWithDatabase
extends ClassBuilder

The SessionWithDatabase interface exposes database operations that operate on a specific database (but not on a specific class or object).

partitionDb

void partitionDb(java.lang.String dbName,
                 java.lang.String clsspacename,
                 int action,
                 int style,
                 PartitionInfo[] info)
Change default storage strategy for a class, index, or internal tables.

Parameters:
dbName - Name of database who storage strategy is to be changed
clsspacename - Name of element whose storage strategy is to be changes
action - Partition action
style - Partition style
info - Partition information array 

 Options for classpacename are:
 

 class name
    Specify the name of a class to change the strategy for storing 
    instance of the class.
    If you have previously specified a clustering of classes, specifying 
    the name of any of the clustered classes will apply the new strategy
    to all of the clustered classes.
 class_name.attr_name
    Specify the index attribute for which you want to change the storage 
    strategy.
    Currently, you can affect the storage strategy for single-attribute 
    indexes only.
 loid2poid
    Specify the keyword "loid2poid" to change the strategy for storing 
    internal database tables that map objects to their current locations
    and status.
 

 Partition action:
 By default, VERSANT creates the same number of logical partitions as the 
 number of database volumes that have been defined. In other words, VERSANT
 defines a logical partition for the system volume and for each storage volume.
 

 Constants.NEW_PARTITION_SCHEMA
    Tell VERSANT that you intend to define a new partition scheme on 
    a class or on the internal tables.
 Constants.NEW_BTREE_PARTITION_SCHEMA 
    Tell VERSANT that you intend to define a new partition scheme on a btree index.
 Constatns.NEW_HASH_PARTITION_SCHEMA
    Tell VERSANT that you intend to define a new partition scheme on a hash index.
 Constants.ADD_PARTITION
    Tell VERSANT to add one new partition to the existing partitions.
    If you specify O_ADD_PARTITION, the style parameter in partitionDb() 
    is ignored.
 

 Partition style:
 When a database needs new pages, VERSANT picks a partition to use for the 
 new pages. There are two allocation algorithms that VERSANT can use: 
 first-available and round-robin.
 

 Constants.FIRST_AVAILABLE
    The first-available algorithm uses the first partition that has 
    enough space for the new pages.
    Partitions are ordered in the sequence in which they were first created.
    If you specify this option, the next partition will be used only when 
    space is exhausted in the partition currently in use.
 Constants.ROUND_ROBIN
    The round-robin algorithm uses the next partition (after the last 
    partition used) that has enough space for the new pages.
    If you specify this option, data pages will be evenly allocated among
    all available partitions.
 

 
 Partition information
 To use partitionDb(), you need to prepare an array of partition information 
 of type PartitionInfo and fill each member of the array with a partition
 name and the corresponding physical volume name.
